article.headline: SE Louisiana 63, Idaho 54
article.story: BOISE, Idaho (AP) -- Nate Lofton scored 15 points and Jonathan Patton added 12 to lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 63-54 victory over Idaho Saturday in the Boise State Invitational tournament. Southeastern Louisiana (2-0) shot 55 percent from the field to hand the Vandals their second loss of the season. Tanoris Shepard had 14 points and Dillon Higdon and Dandrick Jones each added 11 for Idaho. Idaho made only 38 percent of its shots and was hampered by 20 turnovers.
